.SH NAME
refind-btrfs-snapshots-status - Show snapshot bootability against detected ESP boot sets


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBrefind-btrfs-snapshots status [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Show the bootability status of every snapshot against every detected boot set.

.PP
This is the diagnostic command for answering "if my /boot breaks, which of my
snapshots are real fallbacks?" It joins the snapshot inventory (from btrfs) with
the boot image inventory (from the ESP) and renders a compatibility matrix.

.PP
Each row is a snapshot; each kernel column shows whether the snapshot's modules
match that kernel's version (fresh) or not (stale). Snapshots in btrfs-mode
embed their own kernel and are marked n/a — staleness is impossible for them.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for status

.PP
\fB--json\fP[=false]
	Output in JSON format

.PP
\fB--unbootable-only\fP[=false]
	Show only snapshots that are stale or unbootable against all boot sets


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--config\fP=""
	config file (default is /etc/refind-btrfs-snapshots.yaml)

.PP
\fB--local-time\fP[=false]
	Display times in local time instead of UTC

.PP
\fB--log-level\fP="info"
	log level (trace, debug, info, warn, error, fatal, panic)


